{{short description|Annual LGBT event in Beirut, Lebanon}}
The '''Beirut Pride''' is an annual [[LGBT pride]] festival and parade held in [[Beirut]], the capital of [[Lebanon]]. Its founder is Hadi Damien.<ref name="cnnqiblawibeirutgaypride">{{cite news|last1=Qiblawi|first1=Tamara|title=Beirut gay pride event a first for Lebanon|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/05/16/middleeast/beirut-gay-pride/|accessdate=May 21, 2017|work=CNN|date=May 16, 2017}}</ref> The inaugural parade was expected to be held on May 21, 2017. It was the first LGBT pride planned in the [[Arab World]],<ref name="reuterslebanonlaunchesarabworld">{{cite news|last1=Kanso|first1=Heba|title=RPT-Lebanon launches Arab world's first gay pride week|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/lebanon-pride-idUSL8N1IJ5HW|accessdate=May 21, 2017|work=Reuters|date=May 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name="libelelibanorganiselapremiere">{{cite news|last1=Houé|first1=Mélanie|title=Le Liban organise la première Gay Pride du monde arabe|url=http://www.liberation.fr/planete/2017/05/20/le-liban-organise-la-premiere-gay-pride-du-monde-arabe_1570854|accessdate=May 21, 2017|work=Libération|date=May 20, 2017}}</ref> but to cope with logistics, organisers shifted the program of the last day into an outdoor picnic overlooking the Mediterranean.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://m.france24.com/en/20170521-gay-lebanese-scrap-pride-event-because-threats?ref=tw_i|title=Gay Lebanese scrap pride event because of threats|last=|first=|date=2017-05-21|work=France 24|access-date=2017-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803005834/http://m.france24.com/en/20170521-gay-lebanese-scrap-pride-event-because-threats?ref=tw_i|archive-date=3 August 2017|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref>

The 2018 edition began on 12 May with a brunch and was planned to continue until 20 May, but the remaining events were cancelled on 15 May after Hadi Damien had been detained, and the General Prosecutor of Beirut ordered the suspension of the activities planned until May 20.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/inside-the-fight-for-lgbt-equality-in-lebanon|title=‘Love Always Wins’: Inside the Fight for LGBT Equality in Lebanon|last=Teeman|first=Tim|date=2018-08-09|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803005834/http://m.france24.com/en/20170521-gay-lebanese-scrap-pride-event-because-threats?ref=tw_i|archive-date=10 August 2018|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref>

