'''Ezra Rumstick''' is a fictional character created by [[James L. Nelson]] for his ''[[Revolution at Sea Saga]]''. He is the best friend of [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb|Isaac Biddlecomb]] and a fierce [[revolutionary]]. He first appears in ''[[By Force of Arms]]'' when [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb|Isaac]] comes across him [[tar]] and [[feather]]ing, not to mention burning, a [[mannequin]] dressed like a [[Great Britain|British]] soldier. He and [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb|Isaac]] are captured soon after by the British police and face death by [[hanging]]. But they escape, and eventually are pressed into labour on board the ''H.M.S. Icarus'' (See ''[[By Force of Arms]]'').

== Character description ==
Rumstick is described in ''[[By Force of Arms]]'' as a great, "jolly bear of a man." He is very large and very strong, and shows it in the first ''[[Revolution at Sea Saga|Revolution]]'' book when he picks up the ''[[H.M.S. Icarus|Icarus']]'' [[Edward Longbottom|boatswain's mate]] and tosses him overboard after seeing how he brutalises the crew members.

Rumstick once mentioned his mother and that she hadn't failed in her duties to read him the [[Bible]], but no other mention is made of her, or the rest of his family. He met [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb|Isaac Biddlecomb]] in 1764 when he signed aboard [[William Stanton (fictional character)|William Stanton's]] ship the ''Providence'', on which Isaac had been working for a year, following the death of his father. (See [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb]])

Ezra Rumstick has a quick temper and a strong sense of justice. He is one of the biggest [[United States|American]] revolutionaries, and always wants to be in the middle of the action, especially when it involves fighting off [[Great Britain|British]] soldiers. He is very disappointed in ''[[The Continental Risque]]'' when he is sent to help [[Lieutenant Roger Tottenhill]] aboard the ''[[Charlemagne]]'', thus missing all the action involved in being on the [[Bahamas|Bahamian]] [[schooner]] with [[Captain Isaac Biddlecomb|Isaac]].

